  "prompt": "What are some examples of websites with great design?",
  "response": "There are many websites known for their outstanding design, showcasing creativity, usability, and aesthetics. Here are some examples across various categories:\n\n1. **Awwwards**: A showcase of award-winning websites, featuring innovative designs and user experiences. (https://www.awwwards.com)\n\n2. **Apple**: Known for its clean, minimalist design that emphasizes products and user experience. (https://www.apple.com)\n\n3. **Dropbox**: Utilizes a simple and intuitive design, making it easy for users to navigate and understand their services. (https://www.dropbox.com)\n\n4. **Airbnb**: Combines stunning imagery with a user-friendly interface, making it easy to search for and book accommodations. (https://www.airbnb.com)\n\n5. **Spotify**: Offers a vibrant, engaging design that focuses on music discovery and user playlists. (https://www.spotify.com)\n\n6. **Medium**: A platform for writers and readers that features a clean, readable layout with a focus on content. (https://medium.com)\n\n7. **The New York Times**: Balances a wealth of content with an elegant layout, making it easy to read and navigate. (https://www.nytimes.com)\n\n8. **Nike**: Combines dynamic visuals with an engaging storytelling approach, showcasing products effectively. (https://www.nike.com)\n\n9. **Eloquens**: A marketplace for business templates that features a clean, responsive design and easy navigation. (https://www.eloquens.com)\n\n10. **Patagonia**: Emphasizes environmental consciousness with a visually appealing and functional design that reflects its brand values. (https://www.patagonia.com)\n\n11. **Trello**: Uses a simple, colorful interface to make project management easy and visually appealing. (https://trello.com)\n\n12. **Slack**: Offers a clean and intuitive design that makes team communication efficient and enjoyable. (https://slack.com)\n\n13. **Behance**: A platform for creatives to showcase their work, featuring a visually stunning layout that highlights portfolios. (https://www.behance.net)\n\n14. **Squarespace**: Showcases its website-building capabilities with beautifully designed templates and a sleek interface. (https://www.squarespace.com)\n\n15. **Canva**: An easy-to-use graphic design tool with a vibrant, user-friendly interface that encourages creativity. (https://www.canva.com)\n\nThese websites exemplify effective design principles such as usability, aesthetic appeal, and responsive layouts, making them excellent references for anyone interested in web design.",
